title: Keith De Casseres
text: Keith De Casseres (27 May 1910 – 23 February 2003) was a Jamaican <a href="Shooting%20sport">sports shooter</a> who represented the <a href="West%20Indies%20Federation">West Indies Federation</a> at the <a href="British%20West%20Indies%20at%20the%201960%20Summer%20Olympics">1960 Summer Olympics</a>. He competed in the <a href="Shooting%20at%20the%201960%20Summer%20Olympics%20%E2%80%93%20Men%27s%2050%20metre%20pistol">50 metre pistol</a> event.
